# ── Build artifacts ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Architecture-specific builds are attached to GitHub Releases manually,
# never committed. Anything here is regenerable.
*.tar.gz
*.tar.xz
*.zip
*.deb
*.rpm
*.AppImage
docker/offline/

# Python
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
*.so
.Python
.venv/
venv/
env/
*.egg-info/
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/

# Build output
build/
dist/
backend/dist/
frontend/dist/
docs/design/

# Node
node_modules/
.cache/
*.local
.npm/

# ── Runtime data (per-host) ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
# All of these are populated at runtime; committing them would leak
# the maintainer's specific node list, traffic stats, or geo databases.
data/
*.db
*.db-journal
*.sqlite
*.sqlite3
*.sqlite3-journal

# Geo databases (downloaded on first boot via scripts/update_geo.sh)
xray
geoip.dat
geosite.dat
*.mmdb

# ── Environment / secrets ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# Maintainer-only files (personal notes, SSH keys, ad-hoc deploy scripts,
# AI-agent project guide). CLAUDE.md is kept local: it has Claude/Serena-
# specific instructions that aren't useful to contributors using other
# tooling, and the architecturally-useful bits live in README.md instead.
notes.md
notes_*.md
keys.md
deploy_2nd.py
CLAUDE.md

# Local backup of the pre-public git history. Kept on the maintainer's
# machine so old commits stay accessible (they reference personal IPs /
# hardcoded creds and are NOT safe to publish), but never pushed.
.git.bak/

# ── Logs ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.log
logs/

# ── IDE / OS noise ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp
*.swo
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini
*~

# ── Agent / AI tooling — never publish memory or local config ────────────────
# These directories store per-developer agent state (Claude Code's session
# memory, Serena's project memories, Cursor's local context). They are
# intentionally outside the project domain — keeping them in git would
# expose private dev workflow / chat history / scratch notes.
.claude/
.serena/
.cursor/
.aider*/
.continue/
.playwright-mcp/

# ── Misc ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
/tmp/
*.tmp
*.bak

# Frontend test coverage / snapshots
coverage/
.vitest/
